{"title_page": "Spirit of the Boogie", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Spirit of the Boogie\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Kool & the Gang]]\n| cover      = Spirit of the Boogie1975.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 1975\n| recorded   = 1975 <small> at  Media Sound Studios, [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]</small>\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Funk]], [[R&B]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 42:33\n| label      = [[De-Lite Records|De-Lite]]\n| producer   = [[Kool & the Gang]]\n| prev_title = [[Light of Worlds]]\n| prev_year  = 1974\n| next_title = [[Love & Understanding]]\n| next_year  = 1976\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Spirit of the Boogie\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Spirit of the Boogie\n | single1date = March 13, 1975\n | single2     = Caribbean Festival\n | single2date = June 1975\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1     = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{Rating|4.5|5}} <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r42569|tab=review |label=\"Kool & the Gang: ''Spirit of the Boogie'' > Review\" |first=Amy |last=Hanson |accessdate=2011-10-28}}</ref>\n|rev2 = [[BBC]]\n|rev2Score = (favourable)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/cxfd/|title=Kool & The Gang Spirit of the Boogie Review|author=Easlea, Daryl|date=2012|publisher=[[BBC]]|website=bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n|rev3 = [[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]\n|rev3Score = (favourable)<ref>{{cite work|url=https://books.google.tt/books?id=JZ4ej5RmWFUC&pg=PA62&dq=Kool+%26+the+gang+Spirit+of+the+Boogie&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi2p5D6ksboAhWkl-AKHSkFAs4Q6AEIJDAA#v=onepage&q=Kool%20%26%20the%20gang%20Spirit%20of%20the%20Boogie&f=false|title=Essential Funk|author=Green, Tony|page=62|volume=19|date=November 2003|publisher=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Spirit of the Boogie''''' is the highly successful sixth studio album released in 1975 by [[Kool & the Gang]]. It can be seen as a follow-up to ''[[Wild and Peaceful (Kool & the Gang album)|Wild and Peaceful]]'' (1973); The instrumental \"Jungle Jazz\" uses the same basic rhythm track heard in \"[[Jungle Boogie]]\", but lets the players improvise on their instruments (saxophone, trumpet and flute). References to earlier works can be noticed (\"Ancestral Ceremony\" contains the line: \"making merry music...\", which was the name of a song from their 1972 album, ''[[Good Times (Kool & the Gang album)|Good Times]]''). \"Spirit of the Boogie\" features Donal Boyce, who was rapping on \"Jungle Boogie\". Some African influence can be felt, and the band even play in a West-Indian style on \"Caribbean Festival\", another instrumental track, with once more lots of room for improvisation.\n\nThe LP cover mistakenly lists \"Cosmic Energy\" as track 4 instead of \"Sunshine and Love\". \"Cosmic Energy\" was actually released on the next album, ''[[Love & Understanding]]''.\n\nIn one of the songs in the album, entitled \"Jungle Jazz\", the repetitive drum beat that is heard after the drum fill at the beginning has been sampled in over 50 songs, including \"[[Don't Walk Away (Jade song)|Don't Walk Away]]\" by [[Jade (American group)|Jade]] and \"[[Pump Up the Volume (song)|Pump Up The Volume]]\" by [[M/A/R/R/S]]; it can also be found as a sample in [[FL Studio|FL Studio's]] files.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing | headline = Side one\n| title1  = [[Spirit of the Boogie (song)|Spirit of the Boogie]]\n| writer1 = Bayyan, Boyce, Kool & the Gang\n| length1 = 4:52\n| title2  = Ride the Rhythm\n| writer2 = Bayyan, Kool & the Gang\n| length2 = 2:55\n| title3  = Jungle Jazz\n| writer3 = Bayyan, Kool & the Gang\n| length3 = 4:43\n| title4  = Sunshine and Love\n| writer4 = Bayyan, Kool & the Gang\n| length4 = 3:46\n| title5  = Ancestral Ceremony\n| writer5 = Bayyan, Kool & the Gang\n| length5 = 3:39\n}}\n{{Track listing | headline = Side two\n| title1  = Mother Earth\n| writer1 = Bayyan, Brown, Kool & the Gang\n| length1 = 5:38\n| title2  = Winter Sadness\n| writer2 = Bayyan, Smith, Kool & the Gang\n| length2 = 5:04\n| title3  = Caribbean Festival\n| writer3 = Bayyan, Kool & the Gang\n| length3 = 9:26\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n* [[Ronald Bell (musician)|Ronald Bell]] \u2013 arrangements, vocals (1), acoustic piano (1, 2, 5, 7, 8), [[clavinet]] (1), [[ARP synthesizer|ARP synth bass]] (1), [[tenor saxophone]] (1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 8), percussion (2, 3, 5, 6), [[ARP synthesizer]] (5, 7, 8), [[kalimba]] (5), alto flute (7)\n* Ricky West \u2013 vocals (1, 2, 5), clavinet (2, 3, 5), acoustic piano (6), [[Moog synthesizer]] (6)\n* [[Claydes Charles Smith]] \u2013 guitar (1, 2, 3, 6, 7, 8), arrangements (8)\n* Kevin Bell \u2013 guitar (2, 6), arrangements (8)\n* [[Robert \"Kool\" Bell]] \u2013 bass guitar (1-8), vocals (1), arrangements (8)\n* [[George \"Funky\" Brown]] \u2013 drums (1-8), vocals (1, 2, 6), percussion (3, 5, 6), acoustic piano (6), arrangements (6, 8)\n* Dennis \"D.T.\" Thomas \u2013 [[alto saxophone]] (1, 2, 3, 6), vocals (1, 2, 5, 7), flute (3), percussion (3, 8), arrangements (8)\n* Otha Nash \u2013 trombone (1, 2, 3, 6, 8), vocals (1, 2, 3, 6), arrangements (8)\n* Robert \"Spike\" Mickens \u2013 trumpet (1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 8), vocals (1, 2), percussion (2, 3, 5, 8), arrangements (8)\n\n;Additional Personnel \n* Don Boyce \u2013 vocals (1)\n* Something Sweet \u2013 backing vocals (5, 6)\n\n===Production===\n* Producers \u2013 Kool & The Gang\n* Recorded and Mixed by Harvey Goldberg\t\n* Overdub Engineers \u2013 Godfrey Diamond, Alec Head, Ray Janos, Terry Rosiello and Ron St. Germain.\n* Mixed at [[Record Plant]] (Los Angeles, CA).\n* Artwork \u2013 Frank Daniel and Diane Nelson \n* Photography \u2013 Henry Arvinger\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Chart (1975)\n! Peak<br>position\n|- \n| US [[Billboard 200|Top LPs & Tape]]\n| 48\n|-\n| US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|Top Soul LPs]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/kool-the-gang/chart-history/BLP/song/316850|title=Kool &